"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-02-18-French-Riviera-s-Menton-celebrates-Olympic-year-with-Lemon-Festival-1ri62RkMixq-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  Menton marked the Olympic year by showcasing lush citrus during a two-week carnival-style festival with giant floats and sculptures of swimmers, tennis, rugby and badminton players, all assembled from lemons and oranges. This year's edition of the annual Lemon Festival, the 90th, celebrates the Paris Olympic Games and was called \\\"Olympia a Menton.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009dAbout 140 tonnes of citrus fruits and nearly 500,000 citruses were used to build and maintain the floats and historical scenes that line the central Bioves Park. Organizers expect up to 200,000 visitors this year.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"